<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-17 00:07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Toyota Prices To Drop  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) -- Japanese carmaker Toyota plans to
reduce prices of vehicles made in Thailand in a bid to raise its
market share here, according to the president of its Thai
subsidiary.
</P>
<P>
   Yoshiaki Muramatsu of Toyota Motor Thailand Co. told a news
conference late Wednesday that the company will be able to cut
prices of its locally produced vehicles by purchasing all of its
parts domestically. Local parts are less expensive than imports
from Japan.
</P>
<P>
   The aim is to boost domestic market share to 35 percent from the
current 29 percent by 2003.
</P>
<P>
   Toyota Motor Thailand uses about 80 percent domestic parts in
its pickups and 55 percent to 87 percent in its passenger car
models.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
