<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police hunt for female fugitive  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROME, N.Y. (AP) - A woman who may have witnessed the shooting of
two men escaped police custody Tuesday, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Ruby Rivera, 20, was being held by state police in a
second-floor interview room when she slipped out of her handcuffs
and walked out, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Rivera was one of four people stopped Tuesday in Rome in a car
matching the description of a vehicle containing witnesses to the
shooting of two Rome men in another car about 12:20 a.m. Tuesday in
Rockland County on the New York State Thruway.
</P>
<P>
   State police would not identify the shooting victims or their
conditions Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Police said 86 grams of crack cocaine were found in the vehicle
pulled over in Rome, leading to drug charges against Rivera and
three others.
</P>
<P>
   The unsuccessful search for Rivera Tuesday night involved a
helicopter, dogs, state troopers, Rome police and officers from
other agencies.
</P>
<P>
   She is described as 5 feet 4 inches tall, weighing about 160
pounds and having long hair pulled back in a ponytail. She was last
seen wearing a white tank top, black bib overalls and no shoes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
