<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tommy Lee Jones Endorses Al Gore  </HEADLINE>
By MIKE FEINSILBER
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- In an affectionate nomination of his old
college roommate, actor Tommy Lee Jones told Democrats on Wednesday
of canoeing and hunting with Al Gore ''and chasing through the
woods with coon dogs in the middle of the night.''
</P>
<P>
   A friend of 35 years, Jones gave an unusual endorsement at the
Democratic National Convention. It barely mentioned politics.
</P>
<P>
   Instead, he recalled the friendship of two young men who roomed
together for four years at Harvard.
</P>
<P>
   Once neither of them could make it home for Thanksgiving, he
said, ''so we made a fire in the venerable old fireplace in our
room, wrapped a big turkey in a couple of rolls of tin foil, and
roasted it right there in our dorm.''
</P>
<P>
   Tipper Gore, he said, could testify that was ''some of the most
ambitious cooking Al Gore has done since then.''
</P>
<P>
   Gore's wife, sitting in the audience, laughed at that.
</P>
<P>
   Turning serious, Jones recalled other times -- the assassinations
of Martin Luther King Jr. and of Robert Kennedy ''and our country's
tragic involvement in Southeast Asia.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I remember how Al struggled to hold on to his faith at a time
when it seemed like America was losing its way,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Mostly, though, Jones, star of movies and television, recalled
their youth in warm terms.
</P>
<P>
   ''When I visited Al in Middle Tennessee, we did the complicated
things you'd expect college students to do,'' he said, ''catching a
loose cow, going canoeing and hunting, and chasing through the
woods with coon dogs in the middle of the night.''
</P>
<P>
   He also recalled shooting pool and watching Star Trek when they
should have been studying.
</P>
<P>
   Others will talk of affairs of state, Jones said with a straight
face. For him the big issues concerning Gore were these: ''Are they
feeding him well? And will the stress of the job hurt him?''
</P>
<P>
   He answered his own questions: ''He has sense enough to eat well
-- and the stress is no problem.''
</P>
<P>
   With that, he said, ''I nominate my friend Al Gore as the next
president of the United States.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-08-17-00 0018 </TRAILER>
