<SUBHEAD>
Lieberman Tells Americans To Elect Gore
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Vice presidential candidate Joseph Lieberman urged
Americans Wednesday night to elect Al Gore to the White House, hailing him
before the Democratic National Convention as a man of ''vision and values'' who
would extend the nation's current prosperity. Lieberman spoke just minutes
before a roll call of the states would nominate Gore as their presidential
standard bearer and launch the ticket on its fall campaign against Republicans
George W. Bush and Richard Cheney.
</P>
