outside the Democratic National Convention after 2,500 demonstrators marched to
the site denouncing police brutality. An altercation broke out as officers tried
to get a truck through an intersection the protesters had blocked. The
protesters began throwing bottles and other objects at the police, who then
charged with batons. Several rubber bullets were fired. A few delegates arriving
for the convention's evening speakers were escorted through the crowd.
