<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wizards 3, Earthquakes 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Bo Oshoniyi recorded a shutout in his
first start of the season for Kansas City as the Wizards beat the
San Jose Earthquakes 3-0 on Wednesday night in Major League Soccer.
</P>
<P>
   Francisco Gomez, Vicente Figueroa and Chris Henderson scored
goals to help the Wizards improve their MLS-best record to 14-6-6.
San Jose has lost six straight to drop to 5-14-8.
</P>
<P>
   Oshoniyi has three career MLS shutouts. In 1996, he had two
shutouts in 13 games for the Columbus Crew.
</P>
<P>
   Gomez opened the scoring in the 17th minute with his second
career goal, Figueroa added his first career goal in the 24th, and
Henderson scored his eighth goal of the year in the 79th.
</P>
<P>
   San Jose dropped to 5-14-8.
</P>
</TEXT>
