<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 4; Nasdaq Off a Fraction  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down four
points in today's early going. Advancers and decliners are evenly
split on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off fractionally and the Standard
&AMP; Poor's 500 Stock Index is up two points.
</P>
<P>
   Some good earnings news likely will provide some support for the
Dow and the high-techs today.
</P>
<P>
   Dow component Hewlett-Packard blew out expectations with its
third-quarter earnings statement, released after the closing bell
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   But, the parent of United Airlines, UAL, is out with a warning
that its quarterly results will fall below earlier estimates.
</P>
<P>
   At the same time, there's little in the way of economic news.
And analysts expect the market to move cautiously ahead of next
week's Federal Reserve meeting.
</P>
