<HEADLINE> Bombs Injure 19 in Latvia  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   RIGA, Latvia (AP) -- Two bombs exploded in a popular department
store in Riga on Thursday evening, injuring at least 19 people,
police said.
</P>
<P>
   Police spokesman Krists Leiskalns said the bombs went off
minutes apart at the downtownn Centrs department store.
</P>
<P>
   The chief of criminal police, Valdis Pumpers, was among those
injured, but police said they did not believe he was the target of
the attack.
</P>
<P>
   No warnings or threats were reported before the explosions, and
police knew of no motive for the bombings, Leiskalns said.
</P>
<P>
   There have been scores of bombings in Riga since Latvia regained
independence from the Soviet Union in 1991, although injuries or
deaths have been rare. Police have attributed most of the blasts to
gangland activity.
</P>
</TEXT>
