<HEADLINE> Brooks Wants To Open Up Mansion  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GOODLETTSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Garth Brooks wants to open his
mansion to the public, but that tomorrow may never come.
</P>
<P>
   Robert Langford, a lawyer for the singer, said the plan is off
the table for now, after more than 100 residents in this Nashville
suburb gathered Wednesday to complain about the traffic the plan
would bring.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't know of a single person in there that was for it,''
