<HEADLINE> Hannah Takes Marilyn Monroe Role  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Daryl Hannah will take on the role made famous by
Marilyn Monroe in ''The Seven Year Itch'' -- but don't expect to get
a look up Hannah's skirt.
</P>
<P>
   The West End stage production won't recreate the 1955 movie's
legendary scene in which Monroe's skirt billows as she stands over
a grate, producer Laurence Myers said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   ''Daryl is not a Monroe impersonator,'' Myers said.
</P>
<P>
   The George Axelrod comedy, which will open in October, tells the
story of a middle-aged married man who fantasizes about the girl
next door while he is alone in the city for the summer.
</P>
<P>
   Myers could not say whether Hannah would take the route of
fellow stars Nicole Kidman, Kathleen Turner and Jerry Hall, who
recently shed their clothes for London theatergoers.
</P>
<P>
   ''I haven't brought her over here to be naked on stage,'' Myers
said. ''She's a wonderful comedy actress, but if the play requires
her to appear naked she won't have a problem with that.''
</P>
