<HEADLINE> Diplomat To Visit Ailing American  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- An American diplomat will be permitted to
visit an ailing Pennsylvania businessman imprisoned in Moscow on
allegations he stole military secrets from the Russians.
</P>
<P>
   The diplomat will call on Edmond Pope on Friday, the State
Department said.
</P>
<P>
   Pope has bone cancer that is in remission.
</P>
<P>
   Russian physicians have agreed to perform additional tests on
Pope at the request of the physician at the U.S. Embassy in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
   But the State Department on Thursday publicly appealed to
Russian authorities to permit an American physician to examine
Pope.
</P>
<P>
   A spokesman, Philip Reeker, again expressed concern about the
health of the American, who was arrested four months ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
