<HEADLINE> Big movers in the stock market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that were moving substantially or trading
heavily Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
   Hewlett-Packard, down $11.25 to $108.75
</P>
<P>
   The second largest U.S. computer maker fell despite
third-quarter earnings that beat Wall Street estimates. In
addition, Hewlett-Packard's board approved a 2-for-1 stock split.
But some analysts expressed concerns that second half sales could
fall.
</P>
<P>
   Oneida, down $3.313 to $13.375
</P>
<P>
   The company completed the purchases of Delco International,
Sakura Inc., and Viners for a combined price of $135 million. In
addition, Oneida reported second quarter earnings of 20 cents a
share, excluding one-time expenses, down from 46 cents a share a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
   Elan Corp., up $5.875 to $59.875
</P>
<P>
   The company said it plans to form a partnership with Biogen to
develop, make and commercialize Antegren, a drug for multiple
sclerosis and Crohn's disease.
</P>
<P>
   NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
   Ciena Corp., up $15.938 to $179.188
</P>
<P>
   The maker of equipment for fiber-optic telephone networks said
its net income in the third quarter ended July 31 was 19 cents a
share, beating the 17-cent consensus estimate predicted by Wall
Street analysts. The company also predicted better-than-expected
fourth-quarter and 2001 earnings.
</P>
<P>
   Amtech Systems, up $4.625 to $14.625
</P>
<P>
   Amtech's shares rose for a second straight day on news the maker
of semiconductor-production equipment had received a $6.4 million
order for 11 diffusion furnace systems from an unidentified
telecommunications company. It's the company's biggest order to
date.
</P>
<P>
   Incyte Genomics, up $19.875 to $88.813
</P>
<P>
   Motorola licensed Incyte's gene sequence databases and gene
patent portfolio. Terms of the deal weren't disclosed.
</P>
</TEXT>
