<HEADLINE> Body parts of woman found in bags, suitcase  </HEADLINE>
AP Photos pursuing
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) - The body parts of a woman were found in the East
and Hudson rivers less than 15 hours apart, officials said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The Medical Examiner's Office determined the pieces were those
of a black or Hispanic woman. Although the body was not badly
decomposed, it was going to take more time to determine how and
when the woman was killed, said spokeswoman Ellen Borakove.
</P>
<P>
   One set of body parts was discovered just before midnight
Wednesday, when a plastic bag was found stuck in the hull of a Con
Edison barge in the East River near 14th Street and the FDR Drive,
police said. The parts contained a left leg from the knee to the
foot, a right thigh, and two arms with no hands.
</P>
<P>
   Around 1 p.m. Thursday, a U.S. Army Corps of Engineers vessel
traveling north in the Hudson River near Battery Park picked up a
blue Samsonite suitcase, police said. Inside, they discovered three
plastic bags containing a head, two hands, a left thigh, and a
right leg below the knee.
</P>
<P>
   Police were handling the investigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
