<HEADLINE> Candle manufacturer to create 555 jobs in Hudson Valley  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SAUGERTIES, N.Y. (AP) - Candle maker Clearly Tech will invest
$6.75 million in its new plant here and create 555 jobs, the Ulster
County Development Corporation announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Clearly Tech, a private label candle manufacturer, will create a
research and development lab, headquarters and manufacturing plant
in the 200,000-square-fdoot, five-building plant formerly operated
by Phillips. Production of 23 million scented candles per year is
scheduled to begin immediately.
</P>
<P>
   The company, with operations in Norcross, Ga., will make 200 new
hires immediately and grow to 555 by the end of five years. The
jobs include production, customer service, design, finance,
marketing and technical positions in the research and development
lab.
</P>
<P>
   Clearly Tech makes candles under labels including Pottery Barn,
Bath &AMP; Body Works, the Gap, and Clairol Herbal Essence. It also has
its own brands including Perfumes Isabell.
</P>
<P>
   The Empire State Development Corp. will provide $500,000 in
grants for the company: a $125,000 interest rate subsidiary grant
and a $375,000 capital grant toward the purchase of equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Saugerties is 41 miles south of Albany.
</P>
</TEXT>
