<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Atlantic City Medical Center lays steel for Heart Institute  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   POMONA, N.J. (AP) - A cardiac care center being built at
Atlantic City Medical Center-Mainland Division took a step forward
Thursday when a 300-ton crane began laying the first steel beams
for the structure.
</P>
<P>
   The $14 million Heart Institute will be the region's only
cardiac surgery center when it opens early next year, ACMC
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   It will consist of two cardiac operating rooms, two cardiac
catheterization laboratories and four cardiac intensive care unit
beds.
</P>
<P>
   ''Residents of southeastern New Jersey who now travel an hour or
more for cardiac surgery services will soon have access to these
services right in their own community,'' said ACMC spokeswoman
Jennifer Tornetta.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
