<HEADLINE> Alexine Wins Feature at Del Mar  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Argentina-bred Alexine won the $70,000
Tim Furlong Memorial Purse in her U.S. debut at Del Mar on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The winner of four of eight races in Argentina, Alexine stayed
just off the pace until passing her rivals in mid-stretch of the
one-mile turf race for fillies and mares 3 and up. Ridden by Alex
Solis and carrying 117 pounds, Alexine was timed in 1:34.58.
</P>
<P>
   The third choice in the eight-horse field, Alexine paid $9.40,
$4 and $2.80.
</P>
<P>
   Beautiful Noise, the 3-2 favorite and high weight at 121 pounds,
finished 1&AMP;frac12; lengths back in second and paid $2.80 and $2.40.
</P>
<P>
   Another length back was Coracle, who led by one-half length
entering the stretch but finished third and paid $2.80 to show.
</P>
