<HEADLINE> Three killed in three-vehicle crash in Warren County  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   KNOWLTON TOWNSHIP, N.J. (AP) - Three people were killed and
three others were injured Thursday when a car crossed the center
line on Route 46 and crashed into a tractor-trailer before spinning
and striking another vehicle, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   The three people in the 1985 Ford Tempo that crossed the center
line and set off the collisions at 12:25 p.m. were pronounced dead
at the scene, according to Warren County prosecutors. The names of
the driver and two passengers in the Tempo were not released
pending notification of their relatives.
</P>
<P>
   The driver of the tractor-trailer, Robin Hyry, 23, of Carlton,
Minn., was not injured, prosecutors said.
</P>
<P>
   The occupants of the third vehicle were identified as Jeanne
Olivo, 36, the driver, and her two passengers, Dorothy Carbone, 71,
and Angela Olivo, 8, all of Staten Island, N.Y. All three were
treated for minor injuries.
</P>
<P>
   The New Jersey State Police and Warren County authorities are
conducting an investigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
