<HEADLINE> Strawberry Released From Hospital  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- New York Yankees outfielder Darryl Strawberry
was released from Columbia-Presbyterian Medical Center on
Wednesday, nine days after a second round of surgery for cancer.
</P>
<P>
   On Aug. 7, doctors removed an ''isolated tumor mass'' near
Strawberry's left kidney. He previously underwent surgery for colon
cancer in October 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Strawberry, 38, was suspended in February for testing positive
for drugs and had hoped to have his suspension reduced and rejoin
the Yankees this season.
</P>
