<HEADLINE> New Hampshire 1, New York 0, 7 Inn.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BRISTOL, Conn. (AP) -- Pitcher Ben Collins scored the game's only
run and outdueled Juan Almonte as New Hampshire beat New York 1-0
in extra innings Thursday night to win the Eastern Regional title
and advance to the Little League World series.
</P>
<P>
   Collins, who struck out 11 and walked two, drew a walk to open
the seventh. He scored all the way from first base when the New
York defense misplayed Jarek Ostrowski's single to right.
</P>
<P>
   ''They took a big gamble, and that won the ballgame for them,''
said Alberbo Gonzalez, manager of the Bronx team.
</P>
<P>
   Collins kept running as the ball was mishandled in right by
Victor Tores. Tores then threw to third base, but Collins scored
easily when Jesus Hernandez couldn't handle the throw.
</P>
<P>
   ''The way this game was being played, it would come down to one
play and that was our only real opportunity,'' said Frank Szumiesz,
manager of the Goffstown, N.H., team.
</P>
<P>
   In the bottom of the seventh, New York had two runners on base,
but Collins struck out Pedro Guzman to end the game.
</P>
<P>
   Almonte, who also struck out 11, finished with a two-hitter in
pitching a complete game. He did not allow a hit until the sixth
when Jonathan Berube singled with one out.
</P>
<P>
   Goffstown is the first team from New Hampshire to reach the
World Series since Bedford accomplished the feat in 1993.
</P>
</TEXT>
