<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-17 23:40 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Trainer, Jockey Winning Combination  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   RUIDOSO DOWNS, N.M. (AP) -- Trainer Jack Brooks and jockey Jacky
Martin, who for years were a formidable team in quarter horse
racing, reunited Thursday and have the top qualifier for next
month's 42nd running of the All American Futurity.
</P>
<P>
   Eyesa Special was clocked in 21.526 seconds in winning his
trial, the fastest time among the 10 horses that qualified for the
$2.4 million All American.
</P>
<P>
   Seventeen trial races were run Thursday to determine the
futurity field, where the winner of the 440-yard sprint on Labor
Day earns $1 million.
</P>
<P>
   Brooks and Martin combined to win six All Americans, the last in
1992 with Dash Thru Traffic. After they split up, Brooks won a
seventh All American with the filly Falling In Loveagain in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   ''He's the best rider going,'' Brooks said of Martin. ''With
Jacky, I have so much confidence.''
</P>
<P>
   Eyesa Special, making only his third start, won the fifth trial
by 1&AMP;frac12; lengths, taking advantage of a 5 mph tailwind to record the
best time of the day.
</P>
<P>
   A rainstorm hit Ruidoso Downs just before the fifth race and
most of the final nine races were run into a headwind. Only one
horse, Eye On Paydirt, qualified after the eighth race. Eye On
Paydirt, a gelding, got into the final spot in the top 10 with a
time of 21.925 in the 15th trial.
</P>
<P>
   Fashionisanattitude, one of four fillies in the finals, had the
second fastest time of 21.690. However, she bled after crossing the
finish line and was taken off the track in a van. Her status for
the futurity was unknown.
</P>
<P>
   The owners of 11 horses paid a $50,000 supplemental fee to get
them into the trials, but only one -- Copper Buff -- made it to the
finals. Copper Buff, winner of four of six races this summer, won
the eighth trial in 21.787, the fourth fastest time of the day.
</P>
<P>
   Brooks also saddled another qualifier in Blazen Maven, a filly
who had the seventh fastest time of 21.873.
</P>
<P>
   The rest of the qualifiers were: First Down N Surfin (21.740);
Ima Royal Winner (21.805); Whosleavingwho (21.828); Beccas Quick
Six (21.908) and Toughest Test (21.921).
</P>
</TEXT>
